(128, 1, '2019-05-10 21:12:42', '2019-05-10 21:12:42', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Debashree Roy is an Indian Film Actress, Dancer, Politician and Animal Rights Activist. she mainly works in Bengali Film Industry. She acted more than 100 films in her career. She is a member of All India Trinamool Congress. She is the maternal aunt of Bollywood actress Rani Mukherjee. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":129,\"align\":\"center\",\"linkDestination\":\"media\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><a href=\"http://localhost/bollywikia/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Debashree-Roy-photo.jpg\"><img src=\"http://localhost/bollywikia/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Debashree-Roy-photo.jpg\" alt=\"Debashree Roy with Prosenjit Chatterjee\" class=\"wp-image-129\"/></a><figcaption>Debashree Roy with Prosenjit Chatterjee</figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Acting career</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Debashree Roy is one of the Most Famous Bengali Film Actress of 90\'s, she was made her debut in Bengali movie Pagol Thakur in 1966. She became a starlet after she was acted in Tarun Majumdar\'s Bengali thriller Kuheli 1971 as a child character. As an young actress, her first film was Arabinda Mukhopadhyay\'s Bengali film Nadi Theke Sagare. In 1982, she appeared in Tarun Majumdar\'s Bengali film Meghmukti. In the same year, she went on to appear in Goutam Mukherjee\'s blockbuster Bengali film Troyee. She was paired with Mithun Chakraborty in the film. The success of the film brought her leading roles in the following Bengali films such as Aparupa, Samapti and Agamikal.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":133,\"align\":\"center\",\"linkDestination\":\"media\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><a href=\"http://localhost/bollywikia/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/maxresdefault.jpg\"><img src=\"http://localhost/bollywikia/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/maxresdefault-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"Debashree Roy movie Shatabdir Galpo\" class=\"wp-image-133\"/></a><figcaption>Debashree Roy movie Shatabdir Galpo</figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Debashree Roy Awards</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Debashree was earned with BFJA Award for Best Actress for the first time for her performance in Indar Sen\'s Bengali film Thikana. She was received the National Film Award for Best Actress as well as BFJA Award for Best Actress for her role in Rituparno Ghosh’s National Award winning Bengali film Unishe April. She collaborated with Rituparno Ghosh for the second time in his National Award winning Bengali film Asukh which once again earned her the BFJA Award for Best Actress.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Politics</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Debashree, currently a Member of the Legislative Assembly from All India Trinamool Congress, successfully contested the West Bengal assembly elections 2011 against CPI(M) candidate and former minister Kanti Ganguly, from the Raidighi.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Controversy</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In 1983, Roy met Indian cricketer Sandeep Patil on the set of Kabhi Ajnabi. She got involved into an affair with the cricketer who was already married at that time. She was rumoured to be the sole reason for the failure of Patil\'s first marriage.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Wiki and Biography</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table\"><tbody><tr><td>Real Name</td><td>Debashree Roy</td></tr><tr><td>Nickname</td><td>Miss Chumki</td></tr><tr><td>Profession</td><td>Actress, Dancer, Politician, Producer, Choreographer</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Personal Life</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table\"><tbody><tr><td>Date of Birth</td><td>8 August 1961</td></tr><tr><td>Age (as in 2017)</td><td>56 Years</td></tr><tr><td>Birth Place</td><td>Kolkata, West Bengal, India</td></tr><tr><td>Zodiac sign/Sun sign</td><td>Leo</td></tr><tr><td>Nationality</td><td>Indian</td></tr><tr><td>Hometown</td><td>Kolkata, West Bengal, India</td></tr><tr><td>Educational Qualification</td><td>Post Graduate</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Height, Weight &amp; Body Measurements</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table\"><tbody><tr><td>Height (approx.) in centimeters</td><td>165 cm</td></tr><tr><td>Height in meters</td><td>1.65 m</td></tr><tr><td>Height in feet inches</td><td>5’ 5”</td></tr><tr><td>Weight (approx.)</td><td>60 kg</td></tr><tr><td>Weight in pounds</td><td>132 lbs</td></tr><tr><td>Eye Colour</td><td>Brown</td></tr><tr><td>Hair Colour</td><td>Black</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Debashree Roy Movies / Filmography</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table\"><tbody><tr><td>Debut Movie</td><td>Jakhan Esechhilem (2013)</td></tr><tr><td>Popular Movie </td><td>Debi (2005)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Family and Relatives</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table\"><tbody><tr><td>Father</td><td>Birendra Kishore Roy</td></tr><tr><td>Mother</td><td>Arati Roy</td></tr><tr><td>Siblings</td><td>6 (all Elder)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Affairs, Boyfriends and Marital Status</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<table class=\"wp-block-table\"><tbody><tr><td>Marital Status</td><td>Divorced</td></tr><tr><td>Affairs/Boyfriends</td><td>Sandee